DAMATURU – The Executive Governor of Yobe state, Mai Mala Buni, in company of Minister of Power, Engr. Abubakar D. Aliyu, today attended the funeral prayer of Hajiya Adama Gadaka ( Magaran Gudi), the mother of Alh. Muhammadu Gadaka, State APC Chairman. Governor Buni prayed for the repose of the soul of the deceased. He described the death of Hajiya Adama as a great loss to the family, Gadaka community and the state. Hajiya Adama died at a time when her wise counselling is needed to guide the Chairman and his siblings and the people of the community. “She had been a source of strength and inspiration to her family and the community which had been instrumental to their decision making” Buni said. Other dignitaries who attended the funeral prayer include the state deputy governor, Hon. Idi Barde Gubana, Members of the National and state Assemblies,Commissioners and party chieftains. Gov. Buni prayed Allah to forgive her shortcomings, grant her aljannatur Firdaus and to the family, the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss.